post_text:
North Union Families,

North Union was approved, as of September 8, 2020, to provide free breakfast and lunch to all students at all campuses under the Summer Food Service Program as published in the August 31st USDA Nationwide waivers. This will continue through December 31, 2020, or until funding runs out.

All students will automatically receive free breakfast and lunch until further notice. Any extras will be charged, like in the past, to family JMC lunch accounts. We encourage all students to take advantage of this opportunity at North Union.

Sincerely,
Travis Schueller, Superintendent

post_text:
It's Game Day!

Good luck to Warrior Football as they open district play at St. Ed's tonight.

Game Notes for Spectators:

- Mask ARE REQUIRED for all spectators by St. Ed's school district.

- The game will be played at Dodger Stadium located at 1930 Elmhurst Ave.

- All fans will enter through the gate on the west side of the stadium, south of the press box. The visitorsâ€™ section is located on the east side of the stadium. After entering, visiting fans will walk along the track to get to the east bleachers. There are restroom facilities located on both sides of the stadium and the concession stand is located on the west side of the stadium. There is parking on the west side of the stadium and along the streets, please do not park on the grass.

- Admission is $5 and spectators are asked to bring exact change.

- Live stream will not be available for this game.

Thank you for following these guidelines and for supporting your North Union Warriors!

North Union Basketball
June 30 at 1:39 PM Â·

Attention Male Athletes:

Summer workouts start tomorrow morning at the high school. See the attached schedule below. Here are a few details:

- We will have two separate workout times, a time for non-baseball atheltes and a time for baseball athletes. This is to help limit additional exposure for those athletes until the baseball season is completed.

- We will break into three different groups and rotate stations. This allows us to follow social distancing guidelines better and provides more opportunities for coaches and atheltes to sanitize equipment and the room.

- Please meet outside of H.S. weight room (east side of school in the alley) tomorrow morning for a meeting before we enter the school.

- Boys basketball open gyms will begin July 6th for non-baseball athletes. Baseball athletes will be able to join in after their season is completed.

post_text:
PROM UPDATE:

We are very sad to say that due to current guidelines/recommendations that schools must follow from state and county public health departments, NUHS (like other schools) are unable to host a traditional school sponsored prom this year. The school made it through a winter storm last year, but unfortunately we haven't made it past the 2020 pandemic guidelines.

However, while our school may not be able to put on prom this year, we have had some quality conversations with our outstanding Post Prom Committee and they are going to provide other options for the students. They will be in touch soon.

While we can't be with you, we still hope you are able to have a safe and enjoyable event.

Go Warriors!

post_text:
GRADUATION UPDATE:

The 2020 NUHS graduation ceremony will not be open to the public.

Each graduate will have a designated number of guests (4) they can bring.

This is necessary to be compliant with the current Iowa regulation on Mass Gatherings that limits a mass gathering to 50% its normal capacity and ensuring six feet of physical distance between individuals or groups.

Our plan was also approved by Emmet County Public Health department.

We are going to tape the event and upload it to the school facebook page if you wish to see it.

post_text:
North Union CSD COVID-19 Update 04/17/20

North Union Community School District sent this bulletin at 04/17/2020 02:27 PM CDT

April 17th COVID-19 School Update

Dear North Union Families:

Today the Governor announced that Iowa schools will remain closed throughout the 2019-20 school year. All spring sports are cancelled and a summer sports decision will be made by June 1. North Union will continue providing voluntary educational enrichment opportunities for all of our students until the end of the school calendar year which is Friday, May 29th. Teachers will continue to check-in with families on a routine basis and push out learning opportunities for all students each week.

Lunches will continue through April 30th, the school district has submitted an application to extend meals through the month of May. More information will be made available as we know more.

Building principals will be in communication with families next week on things such as locker clean out plans, school events, and all end of the year procedures.

Stay Safe,

Travis Schueller
Superintendent

post_text: Good Luck Warrior Basketball in the postseason!
shared_text:
North Union Basketball
February 17 at 6:17 PM Â·

The boys district game for tonight at Sioux Central has been postponed due to dangerous travel and poor weather conditions. The game has to be made up on Tuesday night due to the next round being on Thursday. We understand this is the same night as our girls regional game and apologize for any inconvenience that causes. Make-up dates are extremely limited come tournament time. Here is what our teams tournament games now look like:

Tuesday, 2/18
- Girls - home vs PAC at 7:00 p.m.
- Boys - at Sioux Central at 8:00 p.m. (15 minutes following the Sioux Central vs Ridge View Girls Regional game which starts at 6:30 p.m.)

If the girls wins, they advance to play the winner of Osage and Lake Mills on Friday, 2/21(at Osage)

If the boys win, they advance to play Emmetsburg at Hull on Thursday, 2/20

#GoWarriors #TourneyTime

The boys district game for tonight at Sioux Central has been postponed due to dangerous travel and poor weather conditions. The game has to be made up on Tuesday night due to the next round being on Thursday. We understand this is the same night as our girls regional game and apologize for any inconvenience that causes. Make-up dates are extremely limited come tournament time. Here is what our teams tournament games now look like:

Tuesday, 2/18
- Girls - home vs PAC at 7:00 p.m.
- Boys - at Sioux Central at 8:00 p.m. (15 minutes following the Sioux Central vs Ridge View Girls Regional game which starts at 6:30 p.m.)

If the girls wins, they advance to play the winner of Osage and Lake Mills on Friday, 2/21(at Osage)

If the boys win, they advance to play Emmetsburg at Hull on Thursday, 2/20

#GoWarriors #TourneyTime

Hats off to all of our Warrior Athletes as they are working together to improve both individually and as a team this summer. Summer is a very busy time for our athletes, especially as a small school with multiple 3 and 4 sport athletes! Keep up the good work Warriors!

post_text:
Congratulations to our Girls Golf Team as they won the conference golf meet today and bring home some hardware for our trophy case! The team was lead by Halle Rezac with a 96, which was good enough for the meets runner-up medalist. The whole team had great rounds and scored as followed:
Jordyn Cummins - 100 (5th place)
Kayla Sabin - 105 (10th place)
Vanessa VonBank - 106
Carys Fuller - 110

Great team win!

Our boys also had a a strong showing as they hosted the conference meet. They came in 5th place and Hayden Nicoson's 82 was the 5th best score of the tournament.

Congratulations players and coaches!
